contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:46.660 --> 01:48.220
[speaking Arabic]

01:48.300 --> 01:52.460
[Khaled Farah in Arabic] <i>I am married,</i>
<i>and I have a daughter.</i>

01:53.900 --> 01:54.940
[speaking Arabic]

01:55.020 --> 01:57.420
<i>Her name is Amal.</i>

01:57.500 --> 01:59.740
Kiss me, kiss me.

02:02.420 --> 02:04.940
Don't give Mom a hard time. Okay?

02:05.020 --> 02:06.100
[Amal crying]

02:06.180 --> 02:09.100
<i>My family is very important to me.</i>

02:10.220 --> 02:13.380
<i>I'm always worrying about them.</i>

02:14.260 --> 02:20.140
I have a strong belief in my work
for the White Helmets.

02:20.220 --> 02:23.740
And every time I'm on a rescue mission,
I think about them.

02:24.220 --> 02:25.500
Abu Omar!

02:27.340 --> 02:28.900
Abu Omar!

02:29.460 --> 02:30.540
[child calls out]

02:30.620 --> 02:34.060
Hello. Where is your dad?
Where is Abu Omar?

02:35.820 --> 02:38.420
-He's ready.
-Is he ready?

02:38.500 --> 02:41.860
Okay, tell him to come down
and we'll go to the center.

02:41.940 --> 02:48.500
The morale of the White Helmets
is always high.

02:49.460 --> 02:54.220
We are always ready
to respond to incidents.

02:55.140 --> 03:01.140
But we just hope that the bombing
and air strikes stop.

03:04.060 --> 03:07.660
Mom, where are you?
Do you need anything?

03:07.740 --> 03:09.140
[woman replies in Arabic]

03:09.220 --> 03:13.340
[Abu Omar] <i>We have to admit</i>
<i>that the situation in Syria</i>

03:13.420 --> 03:16.180
<i>is going from bad to worse.</i>

03:16.260 --> 03:20.180
<i>There is no solution on the horizon.</i>

03:21.900 --> 03:25.940
<i>The situation is sad.</i>
<i>Syria is sad.</i>

03:32.380 --> 03:34.300
[Mohammed Farah reading]

03:39.020 --> 03:42.420
[Mohammed] <i>Before joining</i>
<i>the White Helmets,</i>

03:42.500 --> 03:44.540
<i>I was with an armed group.</i>

03:45.260 --> 03:49.860
<i>I fought for the opposition</i>
<i>for three months.</i>

03:50.340 --> 03:56.260
<i>But I saw that the regime's campaign</i>
<i>was targeting civilians.</i>

03:56.340 --> 04:01.860
And I thought, "It is better to do
humanitarian work than to be armed.

04:01.940 --> 04:07.740
Better to rescue a soul
than to take one."

04:07.820 --> 04:11.140
[indistinct chatter]

04:19.260 --> 04:20.779
[all speaking Arabic]

04:28.900 --> 04:30.100
[man laughs]

04:31.540 --> 04:33.100
[men continue speaking Arabic]

04:33.180 --> 04:34.900
[aircraft approaching]

04:39.060 --> 04:42.100
[indistinct radio chatter]

04:44.420 --> 04:45.980
[yelling in Arabic]

04:57.180 --> 04:58.780
It's the Russians.

05:01.700 --> 05:03.180
[man] Come on, guys, quickly!
Go! Go!

05:03.260 --> 05:04.940
[horn honking]

05:16.220 --> 05:17.740
[man speaking Arabic]

05:17.820 --> 05:19.740
[honking continues]

05:25.300 --> 05:27.020
[speaking Arabic]

05:27.100 --> 05:29.500
[indistinct chatter]

05:34.420 --> 05:36.220
Make a turn and come back!

05:37.460 --> 05:44.260
We, the White Helmets, are the first
to arrive when there is bombing.

05:44.340 --> 05:46.980
-[indistinct chatter]
-[children crying]

05:51.260 --> 05:53.420
[clamoring]

06:04.980 --> 06:11.340
[Abu Omar] <i>If you don't have some courage,</i>
<i>you wouldn't continue doing what we do.</i>

06:12.260 --> 06:13.420
[man] Go here!

06:15.980 --> 06:20.700
Any human being,
no matter who they are

06:20.780 --> 06:24.460
or which side they're on,

06:24.540 --> 06:28.300
if they need our help...

06:29.100 --> 06:32.020
<i>it's our duty to save them.</i>

06:35.660 --> 06:39.420
[Khaled] Does anybody need rescuing?

06:39.500 --> 06:41.060
There's nothing. Right?

06:41.140 --> 06:45.460
Abu Feras lives there,
but I don't know whether he was in or out.

06:45.540 --> 06:46.980
-[Khaled] Here?
-He's got an iron door.

06:47.060 --> 06:48.460
We can't get a sense
if he's in or not.

06:48.540 --> 06:52.180
[both speaking Arabic]

06:52.260 --> 06:54.380
Can we get in via your balcony?

06:54.460 --> 06:57.820
<i>Whenever I'm on a rescue,</i>

06:57.900 --> 07:01.060
I try as hard as possible

07:01.140 --> 07:05.420
to save every person under the rubble,

07:05.500 --> 07:08.500
whether they are young or old.

07:10.820 --> 07:15.420
I consider them all

07:15.500 --> 07:19.420
to be my family.

07:19.500 --> 07:21.780
He usually goes out during the day
and comes back at night.

07:21.860 --> 07:23.740
[Khaled] Okay, there's
nothing more upstairs, right?

07:23.820 --> 07:25.620
There's nothing,
but just check on Abu Mahmoud.

07:27.980 --> 07:29.260
Abu Mahmoud!

07:33.340 --> 07:35.060
[speaking Arabic]

07:39.260 --> 07:41.260
-There's no one here.
-[Khaled] Thank God.

07:41.340 --> 07:43.460
[continues speaking indistinctly]

07:43.540 --> 07:48.940
Brother, ask people about him
and keep an eye out for him.

07:49.020 --> 07:51.180
Don't forget about him.

07:51.260 --> 07:54.740
Whatever you need,
we're the White Helmets.

07:57.580 --> 07:59.100
[Abu Omar speaking Arabic]

07:59.180 --> 08:04.420
There are a number of injuries
and possibly two people killed.

08:11.940 --> 08:14.820
No, there is nothing more.
We're heading back to the center.

09:02.380 --> 09:03.660
[indistinct chatter]

09:16.540 --> 09:19.300
I have been with the White Helmets
for three years.

09:19.380 --> 09:22.060
I've seen many people
who have died in bombings.

09:22.140 --> 09:25.380
I've also seen many people
who were rescued alive.

09:25.460 --> 09:27.260
[indistinct chatter]

09:27.340 --> 09:32.580
Abu Waleed, give me a crowbar!
I want to look under the mattress.

09:33.500 --> 09:35.380
[indistinct chatter continues]

09:38.740 --> 09:41.900
[Khaled] <i>But the hardest thing</i>
<i>is seeing dead bodies.</i>

09:43.940 --> 09:46.500
<i>This affects me a lot.</i>

09:46.580 --> 09:50.780
Guys, don't come closer.
Get me a corpse bag.

09:50.860 --> 09:54.340
But this is my duty and my job.

09:55.620 --> 09:59.060
I have to do it for the people,
for the civilians.

09:59.140 --> 10:01.700
Only her relatives, please.

10:03.700 --> 10:06.660
[man] People who are not doing anything,
please leave.

10:07.980 --> 10:09.940
[indistinct chatter]

10:13.260 --> 10:15.060
[man] Her hand is stuck.

10:15.140 --> 10:17.380
[indistinct chatter continues]

10:42.420 --> 10:44.460
[aircraft approaching]

10:59.220 --> 11:00.940
[clamoring]

11:01.020 --> 11:02.620
[explosion]

11:02.700 --> 11:04.340
[man 1] They've struck!

11:06.980 --> 11:08.300
[man 2] Get down!

11:11.980 --> 11:13.260
[man 1] On the ground!

11:15.060 --> 11:16.900
[clamoring]

11:17.820 --> 11:19.420
[explosions]

11:20.340 --> 11:22.300
[clamoring continues]

11:26.820 --> 11:28.820
[engine starting]

11:28.900 --> 11:30.820
[man yelling in Arabic]

11:36.260 --> 11:38.060
[siren wailing]

11:38.140 --> 11:43.100
[Mohammed] <i>The situation is very difficult</i>
<i>in Syria right now.</i>

11:43.180 --> 11:48.180
<i>Especially with Russia's intervention</i>
<i>to support the regime.</i>

11:48.260 --> 11:52.540
<i>They say that they are fighting ISIS,</i>

11:52.620 --> 11:57.660
<i>but they are targeting civilians.</i>

11:57.740 --> 12:02.100
The casualties are rising daily.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.620
The bloodbath is not stopping.

12:05.820 --> 12:07.860
[siren wailing]

12:07.940 --> 12:09.700
[horn honking]

12:09.780 --> 12:15.180
I've lost two colleagues
very dear and precious to my heart.

12:19.420 --> 12:23.660
They were taking part
in a rescue of civilians.

12:24.780 --> 12:26.380
[explosion]

12:29.660 --> 12:33.980
<i>A week before, we had all been together,</i>
<i>working, eating and drinking...</i>

12:34.060 --> 12:36.740
and then they were dead.

12:36.820 --> 12:38.780
[clamoring]

12:38.860 --> 12:41.180
[Abu Omar] <i>Many of my colleagues</i>
<i>have been killed.</i>

12:42.740 --> 12:45.700
In Aleppo city alone,
we've lost 30...

12:45.780 --> 12:48.540
Thirty White Helmets.

12:49.340 --> 12:51.380
[boy exclaiming sadly]

12:56.340 --> 13:00.420
All lives are precious and valuable.

13:01.340 --> 13:06.300
A child, even if he is not my son,
is like my son.

13:06.900 --> 13:08.460
I cannot explain it.

13:08.540 --> 13:15.140
As an example, I'll tell you a story
that happened to us in Aleppo.

13:16.740 --> 13:21.260
Two barrel bombs were dropped
in the Al-Ansari area.

13:27.060 --> 13:30.860
<i>The first one left</i>
<i>a number of people wounded,</i>

13:30.940 --> 13:36.140
<i>but the second barrel bomb</i>
<i>killed a lot of people.</i>

13:36.980 --> 13:39.100
We went into the area.

13:40.020 --> 13:44.380
It was like a small village
made of ten houses,

13:44.460 --> 13:48.260
<i>and all the buildings</i>
<i>had been leveled to the ground.</i>

13:49.500 --> 13:52.780
<i>On that day,</i>
<i>our work was very hard</i>

13:52.860 --> 13:57.020
and we worked for about 16 hours.

13:58.780 --> 14:03.940
[Abu Omar] <i>I thought that I</i>
<i>was searching under the rubble</i>

14:04.020 --> 14:09.220
for a baby that had died.

14:10.700 --> 14:13.740
<i>But all glory is to God.</i>

14:13.820 --> 14:18.340
<i>We were not meant to leave the area</i>
<i>without hearing a sound.</i>

14:18.860 --> 14:20.420
When I heard the sound of a baby...

14:20.500 --> 14:21.540
[baby crying]

14:21.620 --> 14:26.260
...my feeling was indescribable.

14:26.340 --> 14:31.940
[Mohammed] <i>This gave us renewed strength</i>
<i>to continue to work.</i>

14:32.020 --> 14:34.700
It gave us hope
that some people were still alive.

14:46.860 --> 14:48.460
[indistinct chatter]

14:53.820 --> 14:57.140
[Abu Omar] <i>After 16 hours</i>
<i>under the rubble,</i>

14:57.220 --> 15:01.100
<i>a baby less than a month old,</i>
<i>still alive...</i>

15:02.060 --> 15:03.500
<i>under the dust...</i>

15:04.860 --> 15:08.380
<i>under the ceilings</i>
<i>that had fallen on him...</i>

15:08.460 --> 15:10.140
[baby crying]

15:11.780 --> 15:13.540
[indistinct chatter]

15:16.060 --> 15:17.900
[people cheering]

15:20.740 --> 15:23.940
[Mohammed] <i>We called him</i>
<i>the miracle baby.</i>

15:24.020 --> 15:30.460
The baby was one week old
and at that time my son,

15:30.540 --> 15:34.100
Abdul Hameed,
was almost two weeks old.

15:34.180 --> 15:40.300
I don't know how it came to my mind,
but I imagined that this was my son.

15:40.380 --> 15:42.620
And I started to cry.

15:42.700 --> 15:45.620
I couldn't hold it in,

15:45.700 --> 15:48.020
and all my colleagues started to cry.

16:18.060 --> 16:20.220
[indistinct chatter]

16:30.980 --> 16:34.260
[speaking Arabic]

16:35.900 --> 16:40.380
The hope is that you guys will convey
the information you're learning

16:40.460 --> 16:45.180
to other White Helmets in Syria.

16:46.860 --> 16:52.980
We are under a lot of pressure right now
to train as many people as we can.

16:55.780 --> 16:57.540
God willing.

16:57.620 --> 16:59.580
[speaking Turkish]

17:06.900 --> 17:13.540
[in Arabic] Today, we will review
listening devices

17:13.619 --> 17:18.579
for locating people
trapped under the rubble.

17:20.900 --> 17:22.700
Can anybody hear me?

17:33.180 --> 17:34.340
Don't move.

17:35.900 --> 17:37.900
[man speaking Arabic]

17:37.980 --> 17:43.700
If you can't hear anything,
move the position of the sensor.

17:45.700 --> 17:52.180
[Khaled] <i>It's a hard feeling,</i>
<i>that you are away from your family...</i>

17:53.740 --> 17:56.180
<i>but life requires sacrifice.</i>

17:58.060 --> 18:03.580
<i>So now we are sacrificing a whole month</i>
<i>to gain expertise.</i>

18:22.980 --> 18:24.740
[indistinct chatter]

18:33.300 --> 18:35.780
[speaking Arabic]

18:35.860 --> 18:41.540
[Abu Omar] <i>This training course means</i>
<i>that we'll gain a lot of experience.</i>

18:42.660 --> 18:45.420
Our job depends on speed
and accuracy

18:45.500 --> 18:47.860
to be able to save lives

18:47.940 --> 18:53.580
and extract victims
from under the rubble.

18:59.860 --> 19:01.900
[man] Is anybody here from Hayyan?

19:02.900 --> 19:05.860
Two White Helmets
were killed from there.

19:05.940 --> 19:11.100
Guys, Marwan
and Ahmad Daboul were killed.

19:11.180 --> 19:13.140
And their brother is injured.

19:13.220 --> 19:17.380
The three are all White Helmets
from Hayyan.

19:20.500 --> 19:22.660
-Today?
-[man] Yesterday.

19:25.100 --> 19:27.900
All White Helmets are targeted.

19:29.220 --> 19:31.620
We're all targets.

19:37.180 --> 19:40.340
We were training on the ropes
when they sent us the news.

19:40.420 --> 19:42.620
Read the opening chapter
of the Qu'ran for their souls.

19:42.700 --> 19:44.180
May God accept them.

19:50.740 --> 19:53.260
[Abu Omar] <i>Everyone knows</i>
<i>the truth about Syria,</i>

19:53.340 --> 19:57.140
<i>but no one's been able to stop</i>
<i>the killing and fighting...</i>

19:57.220 --> 20:01.860
or stop the bloodshed and the massacres
that are being committed.

20:09.460 --> 20:11.060
[anchor speaking Arabic on TV]

20:11.140 --> 20:17.140
[man on phone] <i>Early reports suggest</i>
<i>15 people have been killed so far.</i>

20:18.820 --> 20:20.980
Is the area populated?

20:22.700 --> 20:27.940
<i>A wedding hall was completely destroyed</i>
<i>and five or six buildings.</i>

20:28.020 --> 20:32.580
Abu Omar wants to talk to you

20:32.660 --> 20:35.820
to check on his brother and son.

20:35.900 --> 20:39.700
They work in that area.

20:41.660 --> 20:42.700
<i>Okay.</i>

20:45.140 --> 20:46.340
Hello.

20:48.540 --> 20:50.180
<i>Hello.</i>

20:50.260 --> 20:55.740
I can't get hold of my brother or my son.

20:55.820 --> 21:01.100
I'm sorry to be bothering you,

21:01.180 --> 21:07.460
but please can you go and check on them
and then update me?

21:07.540 --> 21:10.900
Just go to my brother's, okay?

21:10.980 --> 21:17.860
And he will find my son.

21:20.420 --> 21:22.740
[reporter speaking Arabic on TV]

21:28.140 --> 21:34.180
This must be the strongest car bomb
to ever hit Aleppo.

21:34.260 --> 21:35.580
I didn't know who was speaking.

21:35.660 --> 21:36.660
Who?

21:36.740 --> 21:37.900
[Khaled] Listen to it.

21:37.980 --> 21:39.820
[speaking Arabic]

21:43.780 --> 21:44.820
My son.

21:45.740 --> 21:46.860
This is my son.

21:50.460 --> 21:53.500
[man] <i>In my whole life, I've never seen</i>
<i>so much destruction.</i>

21:55.020 --> 21:57.020
This is my son.

21:57.100 --> 21:59.180
[Khaled] Yeah, thank God.

21:59.260 --> 22:02.020
But, brother,
what's really the difference

22:02.100 --> 22:06.220
between my son
and another person's?

22:06.300 --> 22:12.780
Aren't they all innocent?
What's their sin, whoever it is?

22:13.700 --> 22:15.980
[Khaled] ISIS on the ground
and the Russian planes from above.

22:16.060 --> 22:18.260
Six buildings...

22:18.340 --> 22:20.740
[men continue speaking Arabic]

22:25.220 --> 22:26.780
I feel cold.

22:26.860 --> 22:28.380
[sighs]

22:46.260 --> 22:47.740
[Khaled] <i>There is no war here.</i>

22:49.100 --> 22:50.620
<i>No devastation.</i>

22:51.540 --> 22:52.860
<i>No destruction.</i>

22:54.300 --> 22:55.700
<i>Just by crossing a border,</i>

22:55.780 --> 22:57.940
<i>it's so strange</i>
<i>how the situation can change.</i>

23:25.500 --> 23:26.740
[Mohammed] If this was in Syria,

23:26.820 --> 23:31.260
it would have been dropping
cluster bombs from that height.

23:31.340 --> 23:32.860
We see so many cluster bombs.

23:32.940 --> 23:34.540
[man] Really?

23:34.620 --> 23:39.380
It would not drop barrel bombs,
because they want to cause more harm.

23:41.700 --> 23:42.740
[man 1] There is a sound...

23:42.820 --> 23:47.540
We can now differentiate between the sound
of military and civilian aircraft.

23:47.620 --> 23:49.620
[man 2] Take shelter, hero!

23:49.700 --> 23:53.700
[laughing] Where would I take shelter
in this building?

23:53.780 --> 23:58.620
If a barrel bomb fell here,
it would destroy the whole building!

23:58.700 --> 24:03.100
My son is almost two years old.

24:03.180 --> 24:04.900
He knows all about the war planes.

24:06.140 --> 24:11.660
When planes fly over
and there's an air strike...

24:11.740 --> 24:15.340
my son jumps up on my lap and says,

24:15.420 --> 24:17.660
"Daddy, a bomb."

24:41.540 --> 24:42.940
[man] <i>Allahu akbar.</i>

24:45.420 --> 24:47.500
<i>Allahu akbar.</i>

24:47.580 --> 24:49.620
[siren blaring]

24:51.220 --> 24:53.700
[man] Now you will learn

24:53.780 --> 24:57.060
how you can give
a practical lesson to the trainees

24:57.140 --> 25:01.300
about putting out fires.

25:01.380 --> 25:03.220
What is the most important thing?

25:04.020 --> 25:05.100
Safety.

25:10.700 --> 25:14.140
[reporter on TV] <i>The suffering</i>
<i>of civilians has entered a new chapter</i>

25:14.220 --> 25:16.300
<i>with Russia's air campaign.</i>

25:16.380 --> 25:21.180
<i>There are record levels of shelling,</i>
<i>especially over Aleppo.</i>

25:21.260 --> 25:25.460
[man on phone] <i>I am telling you,</i>
<i>about 200 air raids a day,</i>

25:25.540 --> 25:30.460
<i>and the new rockets</i>
<i>are not like the old ones.</i>

25:31.380 --> 25:33.540
Two hundred air raids a day?

25:33.620 --> 25:37.020
<i>And every rocket</i>
<i>is ruining a full neighborhood.</i>

25:38.020 --> 25:40.020
[men speaking Arabic]

25:48.940 --> 25:51.060
[men shouting on phone]

25:55.540 --> 25:59.100
"You, White Helmets,
you are heroes. May God protect you."

25:59.180 --> 26:02.100
I am really worried,

26:02.180 --> 26:07.740
but I trust in God to protect my family
and my colleagues.

27:01.180 --> 27:03.220
[reporter in English]
<i>The latest slaughter in Syria</i>

27:03.300 --> 27:05.980
<i>is a war crime, say France and Turkey.</i>

27:06.060 --> 27:08.980
<i>For the UN, missile attacks</i>
<i>on hospitals and schools</i>

27:09.060 --> 27:12.940
<i>in rebel-held areas</i>
<i>that left up to 50 civilians dead</i>

27:13.020 --> 27:14.860
<i>were a violation of international law.</i>

27:14.940 --> 27:18.140
<i>Médecins Sans Frontières says</i>
<i>either the Syrian government,</i>

27:18.220 --> 27:21.060
<i>or its main supporter Russia,</i>
<i>was responsible...</i>

27:21.140 --> 27:23.220
[indistinct chatter]

27:25.500 --> 27:27.260
[Abu Omar in Arabic]
His brother is under the rubble,

27:27.340 --> 27:29.020
but his condition is not known yet.

27:29.100 --> 27:30.740
[man] Three people
are still under the rubble.

27:32.220 --> 27:33.620
Him and two of his colleagues.

27:33.700 --> 27:36.380
They were able to pull one out.

27:36.460 --> 27:39.140
There were four
in the hospital laboratory.

27:39.220 --> 27:42.660
They got one out,
but three are left.

27:42.740 --> 27:47.580
They just sent an announcement
with their names.

27:50.300 --> 27:54.100
I want him to cry.
It's better.

27:54.180 --> 27:56.900
I was in a situation similar to Abu Zaid.

27:56.980 --> 27:59.220
My brother was killed
five months ago.

27:59.300 --> 28:03.140
I had a training course
like this one in Istanbul.

28:03.220 --> 28:08.060
I went there and arrived in the morning.
You know, it's a long way.

28:08.140 --> 28:09.220
I slept a few hours.

28:09.300 --> 28:12.420
When I awoke, I asked my friend
to open the Internet for me,

28:12.500 --> 28:14.220
as I didn't know how.

28:15.260 --> 28:17.420
I had my brother's phone at the time.

28:17.500 --> 28:19.100
I got online
and saw my brother's photo. Dead.

28:19.180 --> 28:21.580
It was the first photo I had looked at.

28:24.060 --> 28:25.380
What's next, Ibrahim?

28:25.460 --> 28:27.500
[Ibrahim] We've stopped.
Done for the day.

28:27.580 --> 28:29.260
We're not able to do any work.

28:29.340 --> 28:31.540
-[Ibrahim] Emotionally, we can't.
-Yes, right.

28:33.060 --> 28:35.740
[man on phone]
<i>We've just got two women out, alive.</i>

28:35.820 --> 28:36.860
<i>Do you understand me?</i>

28:36.940 --> 28:41.820
<i>And we got out Allaa Al-Halak</i>
<i>and another one with him, dead.</i>

28:43.340 --> 28:47.220
Are you just listening
or are you speaking with him?

28:47.300 --> 28:49.060
[man] You talk with him, Abu Basheer.

28:51.900 --> 28:53.220
Oh, Hamid.

28:54.540 --> 28:58.500
Can you hear me?
I'm Abu Basheer.

28:58.580 --> 29:01.260
Tell us the news.
Has Abu Karmu been killed

29:01.340 --> 29:02.940
or have you pulled him out alive?

29:03.020 --> 29:04.500
Just tell us.

29:04.580 --> 29:07.340
His brother is confused
and does not know what to do.

29:08.820 --> 29:11.900
[Hamid] <i>Abu Basheer, just be patient</i>
<i>for 30 minutes more,</i>

29:11.980 --> 29:13.540
<i>and then call me back.</i>

29:14.140 --> 29:18.700
<i>I just spoke with the guys</i>
<i>to find out if people are still alive.</i>

29:18.780 --> 29:19.820
[knocking on door]

29:19.900 --> 29:21.060
<i>Listen to me.</i>

29:21.140 --> 29:23.380
<i>There were two killed.</i>

29:23.460 --> 29:25.700
[all speaking in Arabic]

29:29.900 --> 29:36.580
He understood from you
that he is dead.

29:36.660 --> 29:39.380
Your brother is our brother.
God bless him.

29:41.100 --> 29:42.820
So you still haven't got him out?

29:43.420 --> 29:44.460
Nothing is clear yet.

29:44.540 --> 29:46.780
Thanks, brother,
and please do your best.

29:46.860 --> 29:51.740
I know we don't need to tell you,
but you are real heroes.

29:51.820 --> 29:54.140
[reporter speaking Arabic on TV]

30:01.620 --> 30:03.580
Today, they hit all the hospitals...

30:05.620 --> 30:07.740
in Aleppo and in Idlib.

30:08.660 --> 30:11.100
Now their targets are the hospitals.

30:11.180 --> 30:14.620
Are these today's victims
from the hospital?

30:14.700 --> 30:16.340
Updated nine minutes ago.

30:19.620 --> 30:21.580
His name is among them.

30:34.340 --> 30:37.820
[Islamic call to worship]

31:23.060 --> 31:24.900
[inaudible]

32:00.540 --> 32:03.300
[Mohammed] <i>Tomorrow will be better.</i>

32:04.820 --> 32:09.740
We are always optimistic
that what's to come is better.

32:09.820 --> 32:12.660
Justice will prevail one day.

32:13.700 --> 32:15.460
[indistinct chatter]

32:26.180 --> 32:29.900
[Abu Omar] <i>Without hope,</i>
<i>what good is life?</i>

32:33.660 --> 32:35.940
<i>People will die without hope.</i>

32:44.540 --> 32:48.740
<i>It's a feeling of happiness.</i>

32:49.380 --> 32:56.180
True happiness, you have to
experience it to understand.

32:56.740 --> 32:58.060
[speaking indistinctly]

32:58.740 --> 33:00.260
[speaking Arabic]

33:09.100 --> 33:10.340
[baby cooing]

33:11.460 --> 33:14.500
[Abu Omar] <i>An indescribable happiness.</i>

33:14.580 --> 33:17.660
<i>A baby that I haven't seen</i>
<i>for a year and a half.</i>

33:20.300 --> 33:22.340
<i>His is a very precious life.</i>

33:25.580 --> 33:28.500
Do you know the feeling that you get
when you plant a small seed

33:28.580 --> 33:31.740
and it grows into a beautiful bush?

33:31.820 --> 33:34.540
<i>That's how we feel</i>
<i>that this baby is still alive</i>

33:34.620 --> 33:36.900
<i>thanks to God and to our work.</i>

33:38.780 --> 33:40.700
<i>We feel very proud.</i>

33:40.780 --> 33:43.260
[indistinct chatter]

33:55.860 --> 33:58.980
<i>Thank God he's alive and doing well.</i>

33:59.060 --> 34:00.980
[speaking Arabic]

34:07.460 --> 34:08.900
[speaking Arabic]

34:10.380 --> 34:14.940
[Abu Omar] <i>I've learned many lessons</i>
<i>from baby Mahmoud.</i>

34:15.020 --> 34:18.540
<i>Patience, persistence, hard work...</i>

34:18.620 --> 34:22.179
and never to lose hope.

34:22.260 --> 34:24.060
If a person is destined to live,

34:24.139 --> 34:26.860
no matter what happens,
they will live.

34:32.940 --> 34:37.540
I have a lot of hopes
for my own daughter.

34:41.540 --> 34:44.179
I have a lot of dreams
for her, actually.

34:46.420 --> 34:51.580
When I come back from work
and I pick her up...

34:52.580 --> 34:56.380
I look at her and I'm very sad

34:56.460 --> 35:00.580
about the fate of children
who lost their lives during the shelling.

35:03.300 --> 35:06.700
But, at the same time,
I wish for her to fulfill her dreams...

35:09.300 --> 35:11.540
and grow up to be
many, many years old.

35:23.860 --> 35:25.420
[inaudible]

35:58.060 --> 36:01.620
[Abu Omar] <i>Every morning, I wake up</i>
<i>and do this work because it's my duty,</i>

36:01.700 --> 36:04.060
<i>my humanitarian duty.</i>

36:04.740 --> 36:07.380
I will never quit
as long as I'm still alive.

36:09.220 --> 36:15.780
I'm willing to sacrifice my soul
for the sake of the people.

36:16.740 --> 36:18.260
This job is sacred.

36:20.700 --> 36:27.060
I am trying to do something
for the people

36:27.140 --> 36:29.020
and for my country.

36:48.860 --> 36:51.900
[Abu Omar] <i>In the White Helmets,</i>
<i>we have a motto...</i>

36:53.940 --> 36:57.980
<i>"To save a life</i>
<i>is to save all of humanity."</i>

